\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the following, to measure quantity indices, information on prices and quantities for consumption, investment and income will be required. The use of the investment good as numeraire, in this framework, is inconsequential. These are the steps to follow in order to measure the needed variables.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\begin_inset Argument listpreamble:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
par 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout
\end_inset

Assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{gt}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{st}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal A}_t$
\end_inset

 all three grow at different constant rates, with 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat A_{g} > \widehat A_{s}$
\end_inset

. In the data, 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat A_{g}$
\end_inset

 is very close to 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat {\cal A}$
\end_inset

. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Use equations (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
