\begin_layout Paragraph
Parameter values.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset

Table
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:parameters"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 shows the parameters values used by Herrendorf et al. (2021) in their quantitative exercise. In the measurement of sectoral total factor productivity (TFP) they have followed a structured approach based on observable economic data. First, sector-specific TFP (
\begin_inset Formula \( A_{jt} \)
\end_inset

), 
\begin_inset Formula $j=\{g,s\}$
\end_inset

, was estimated using data from WORLD KLEMS on real value added, capital and labor inputs. Given the aggregate capital share 
\begin_inset Formula \( \theta \)
\end_inset

, they computed the sectoral TFP growth rates using 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\widehat{A}_{jt} = \widehat{Y}_{jt} - \theta \widehat{K}_{jt} - (1 - \theta) \widehat{L}_{jt}, \quad j \in \{g,s\},
\]
\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat x$
\end_inset

 measures the growth rate of variable 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

. All variables except 
\begin_inset Formula \( \widehat{A}_{jt} \)
\end_inset

 are directly observable. Normalizing initial TFP levels to 
\begin_inset Formula \( A_{j0} = 1 \)
\end_inset

, they use the estimated growth rates to construct the time series for 
\begin_inset Formula \( A_{jt} \)
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Next, they estimated aggregate investment-specific TFP (
\begin_inset Formula \( A_{xt} \)
\end_inset

). Again, setting the initial condition 
\begin_inset Formula \( A_{x0} = 1 \)
\end_inset

, they computed its growth rates using 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\widehat{A}_{xt} = \widehat{X}_t - \frac{P_{gt} X_{gt}}{X_t} \widehat{X}_{gt} - \frac{P_{st} X_{st}}{X_t} \widehat{X}_{st},
\]
\end_inset

where all components at the right-hand-side of this equation are observable. 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
%Finally, we assess the theoretical conditions required to ensure the existence of an aggregate balanced growth path (ABGP).
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

